The paper deals with the problem of answering functional aggregate queries in databases and relational machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (databases) and cs.LG (machine learning) sub-categories. The use of tree decompositions and hypertree width parameters indicates a possible connection to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on optimization problems and the use of submodular functions suggests a possible connection to the cs.DM (discrete mathematics) sub-category.
